msgctxt "44_Uda"
msgid "So, Haruka-san, have you ever done one of these handshake events before?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56_Haruka"
msgid "No, this is my first time."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68_Uda"
msgid ""
"I see. That's all right. Well, let me give you a little\r\n"
"rundown of how it's going to go."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80_Uda"
msgid ""
"To raise fan satisfaction level, shake hands with as many fans as you can "
"before time runs out. At the same time, make sure to keep an eye on the "
"staff member who keeps the line of fans moving along. Lastly, be on the "
"lookout for super fans wearing happi coats. They can raise the satisfaction "
"level more than regular fans, but if disappointed, they can also lower it "
"dramatically.\r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92_Uda"
msgid ""
"While it's important to shake hands with each fan for as long as possible, "
"the line must also be kept moving. This is the job of a staff member named "
"Taro Hagashi, known as \"The Remover.\" He discourages fans from lingering "
"too long and removes them if necessary.\r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "104_Uda"
msgid ""
"A fan who is removed leaves in fear, and the fan satisfaction level drops. "
"Luckily, \"The Remover\" is also a big fan of yours. Use "
"<Action:Button_L1@Handshake> to flash him a smile and he'll turn to mush "
"and forget to do his job. You can use this to your advantage by smiling at "
"the right time.\r\n"
" \r\n"
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "116_Uda"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"When the command to shake hands appears on the screen, hold down "
"<Action:Button_Square@Handshake>. You will continue to shake hands with the "
"fan until you release <Action:Button_Square@Handshake>. During this time, "
"the fan will speak to you. Use "
"<Action:Button_DPad_Left@Handshake><Action:Button_DPad_"
"Right@Handshake><Action:Button_DPad_Up@Handshake><Action:Button_DPad_"
"Down@Handshake> to choose your response. To raise the fan satisfaction "
"level, choose the reply that matches the color of the fan's comment.\r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
" \r\n"
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
" "
msgstr ""

msgctxt "128_Uda"
msgid ""
"And that's about it... So, in a nutshell, we'd like you to\r\n"
"meet as many guests as possible in the time that we have,\r\n"
"and do your best to make them all happy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "140_Uda"
msgid ""
"The best way to make 'em happy is by shaking hands with each\r\n"
"one of them for as long as you can and carefully responding\r\n"
"to what they say."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "152_Haruka"
msgid ""
"I think you mentioned something about \"removing,\" but could\r\n"
"you explain what that means?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "164_Uda"
msgid ""
"Oh, that. Well, if a handshake goes on a little too long,\r\n"
"one of our staff will help move that fan along. In this\r\n"
"business, we call that \"removing.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "176_Uda"
msgid ""
"It's an unfortunate necessity due to the nature of the\r\n"
"event. What's more, fans who get \"removed,\" of course, feel\r\n"
"disappointed and overall satisfaction drops."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "188_Uda"
msgid ""
"You'll want to shake their hands for as long as possible,\r\n"
"but make sure you stop before they need to be \"removed.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "200_Haruka"
msgid ""
"I see. Phew, there's a lot more to these events than I\r\n"
"thought..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "212_Uda"
msgid ""
"By the way, that guy over there is the one in charge of\r\n"
"monitoring the guests. He's \"The Remover.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "236_The Remover"
msgid ""
"Don't you worry! I'll defend your safety with my very life\r\n"
"if need be! Say the word, and they're outta here!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "248_Haruka"
msgid ""
"Huh? Uh, thank you... As long as you don't get too carried\r\n"
"away..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "260_Uda"
msgid ""
"And that just about covers it. Would you like for me to go\r\n"
"through it again?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "272_Haruka"
msgid "Yes, please, if you wouldn't mind."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "284_Uda"
msgid "Not at all! All right. Here we go, from the top."
